com.appboy

Class AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.appboy.AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.app.Application.ActivityLifecycleCallbacks

    public class AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.app.Application.ActivityLifecycleCallbacks
    Can be used to automatically handle Braze lifecycle methods. Optionally, openSession() and closeSession() are called on onActivityStarted and onActivityStopped respectively. The InAppMessageManager methods of registerInAppMessageManager() and unregisterInAppMessageManager() can be optionally called here as well.

        public AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener(boolean sessionHandlingEnabled,

        public AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener(java.util.Set<java.lang.Class<?>> inAppMessagingRegistrationBlocklist,
                                       java.util.Set<java.lang.Class<?>> sessionHandlingBlocklist)
        Constructor that sets a blocklist for session handling and AppboyInAppMessageManager registration while also enabling both features.
        Parameters:
        inAppMessagingRegistrationBlocklist - A set of Activitys for which in-app message registration will not occur. Each class should be retrieved via Object.getClass().

      • AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener

        public AppboyLifecycleCallbackListener(java.util.Set<java.lang.Class<?>> inAppMessagingRegistrationBlocklist)
        Constructor that only sets a blocklist for AppboyInAppMessageManager registration and enables AppboyInAppMessageManager registration. Session handling is enabled and has an empty blocklist.
        Parameters:
        inAppMessagingRegistrationBlocklist - A set of Activitys for which in-app message registration will not occur. Each class should be retrieved via Object.getClass(). If null, an empty set is used instead.
